THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 331 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Administrator, in coordination with the Museum
4 Director of the Nevada State Museum, may rent or lease rooms in
5 the Capitol Building for the purpose of holding an event.
6 2. The Administrator shall charge a fee for the rental or lease
7 of a room pursuant to subsection 1.
8 3. Any money the Administrator receives pursuant to
9 subsection 2:
10 (a) Must be deposited in the State Treasury and accounted for
11 separately in the State General Fund;
12 (b) May be used by the Administrator only for maintenance of
13 the Capitol Building; and
14 (c) Does not revert to the State General Fund at the end of
15 each fiscal year.
16 4. Any interest or income earned on the money in the
17 account, after deducting any applicable charges, must be credited
18 to the account. Any claims against the account must be paid as
19 other claims against the State are paid.
20 5. The Administrator shall adopt regulations necessary to
21 carry out the provisions of this section.
22 Sec. 2. NRS 331.010 is hereby amended to read as follows:
23 331.010 As used in NRS 331.010 to 331.145, inclusive, and
24 section 1 of this act, unless the context otherwise requires:
25 1. “Administrator” means the Administrator of the Division.
26 2. “Buildings and Grounds Section” means the Buildings and
27 Grounds Section of the Division.
28 3. “Department” means the Department of Administration.
29 4. “Director” means the Director of the Department.
30 5. “Division” means the State Public Works Division of the
31 Department.
32 Sec. 3. NRS 331.190 is hereby amended to read as follows:
33 331.190 [Any]
34 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, any person
35 who sells, barters, gives, or in any way disposes of any spirituous or
36 malt liquors, wines or cider, of any description whatever, within the
37 Capitol Building of this state, shall be guilty of a misdemeanor.
38 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to an event that
39 is held in the Capitol Building pursuant to section 1 of this act.
